    "body": "Yeah, for reasons due with RN architecture we couldn't have it the way I intended to and now I'm beginning to consider the alternatives. What I'd propose is to get us moving on with searching message history and remove the animation, searchbar remains fixed at the beginning of chats list, dapps get their own tab and we remove browser results in search. To me the search right now is very beta and I'd like to move forward here.\r\n\r\nIn the current implementation, scrolling up should remove the searchbar, inverse to how scrolling down shows it. In addition it should only work when you're at the beginning of the list so the search is shown during the overdrag behaviour.",
